# preg_match() – First Match

`preg_match(string $pattern, string $subject, array &$matches = null, int $flags = 0, int $offset = 0): int|false` returns 1 if the pattern matches, 0 if not, or false on error.

```php
<?php
if (preg_match("/php/i", "I love PHP")) {
    echo "Found!";
}
// The 'i' modifier makes it case-insensitive
?>
```

If `$matches` is provided, it will be filled with the matches.

```php
<?php
$str = "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.";
if (preg_match("/quick.*fox/", $str)) {
    echo "Match found!\n";
}

// Capture the word after 'brown'
preg_match("/brown (\w+)/", $str, $matches);
print_r($matches); // [0 => "brown fox", 1 => "fox"]
?>
```
